## Styling Patterns

### Utility Classes
- Use `cn()` utility from [src/lib/utils](mdc:src/lib/utils) for conditional classes
- Follow Tailwind CSS naming conventions
- Use semantic class names when possible
- Maintain consistent spacing and typography

### Responsive Design
```typescript
// Mobile-first responsive design
<div className="p-4 md:p-6 lg:p-8">
  <h1 className="text-xl md:text-2xl lg:text-3xl">Title</h1>
</div>
```

### Dark Mode Support
- Use Tailwind's dark mode utilities
- Test components in both light and dark themes
- Use CSS custom properties for theme values
- Ensure proper contrast ratios

## Data Visualization

### Nivo Charts Integration
- Use Nivo components for data visualization
- Implement responsive chart containers
- Handle loading and error states
- Provide accessible chart descriptions

### Chart Components
```typescript
// Example chart component structure
import { ResponsiveBar } from '@nivo/bar';

interface ChartProps {
  data: Array<{ id: string; value: number }>;
  title: string;
}

export default function ChartComponent({ data, title }: ChartProps) {
  return (
    <div className="h-64 w-full">
      <h3 className="mb-4 text-lg font-semibold">{title}</h3>
      <ResponsiveBar
        data={data}
        keys={['value']}
        indexBy="id"
        margin={{ top: 20, right: 20, bottom: 50, left: 60 }}
        padding={0.3}
        colors={{ scheme: 'nivo' }}
        axisBottom={{
          tickSize: 5,
          tickPadding: 5,
          tickRotation: 0,
        }}
        axisLeft={{
          tickSize: 5,
          tickPadding: 5,
          tickRotation: 0,
        }}
      />
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Form Components
Use react-hook-form when possible.

### Input Components
- Use consistent input styling
- Implement proper validation states
- Provide clear error messages
- Support accessibility features

### Button Components
- Use consistent button variants
- Implement loading states
- Support different sizes and colors
- Ensure proper focus states

## Layout Components

### Container Components
- Use consistent max-widths
- Implement proper padding and margins
- Support different screen sizes
- Maintain visual hierarchy

### Grid and Flexbox
- Use CSS Grid for complex layouts
- Use Flexbox for simple alignments
- Implement responsive breakpoints
- Maintain consistent spacing

## State Management

### Local State
- Use React hooks for local component state
- Implement proper state updates
- Handle loading and error states
- Use optimistic updates when appropriate

### Global State
- Use React Query for server state
- Use Context for truly global state
- Implement proper state persistence
- Handle state synchronization

## Performance Optimization

### Component Optimization
- Use `React.memo()` for expensive components
- Implement proper key props for lists
- Use `useCallback` for event handlers
- Use `useMemo` for expensive calculations

### Lazy Loading
- Lazy load non-critical components
- Use dynamic imports for code splitting
- Implement proper loading states
- Optimize bundle size

## Accessibility

### ARIA Attributes
- Use proper ARIA labels and descriptions
- Implement keyboard navigation
- Provide focus indicators
- Test with screen readers

### Semantic HTML
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Implement proper heading hierarchy
- Use descriptive alt text for images
- Ensure proper color contrast

